elements.title: half a square mile (130 ha) in Alberta

elements.title: Bethlehem, Georgia
elements.contents: ... that a new Christmas stamp that debuted in the 350-person town of Bethlehem, Georgia, in 1967 got so much attention that the two-employee post office had to hire 43 temporary workers?

elements.title: Horace Archambeault
elements.contents: ... that Horace Archambeault introduced a Quebec bill in 1904 that would make employers responsible for workplace accidents, even if they were not negligent?
